exercises.name: Squat
exercises.form_notes: Brace core, break at hips and knees together, drive through whole foot

exercises.name: Bench Press
exercises.form_notes: Retract shoulder blades, arch upper back, drive feet into floor

exercises.name: Deadlift
exercises.form_notes: Brace hard, push floor away, lock hips and knees together at top

exercises.name: Overhead Press
exercises.form_notes: Squeeze glutes, press straight up, move head through at lockout

exercises.name: Barbell Row
exercises.form_notes: Hinge at hips ~45 degrees, pull to lower chest, control descent

exercises.name: Front Squat
exercises.form_notes: Elbows high, upright torso, brace core throughout

exercises.name: Romanian Deadlift
exercises.form_notes: Slight knee bend, hinge at hips, feel stretch in hamstrings

exercises.name: Incline Bench Press
exercises.form_notes: Set bench to 30-45 degrees, same cues as flat bench

exercises.name: Close-Grip Bench Press
exercises.form_notes: Hands shoulder-width, tuck elbows, emphasize tricep lockout

exercises.name: Barbell Curl
exercises.form_notes: Keep elbows pinned at sides, full range of motion, no swinging

exercises.name: Dumbbell Bench Press
exercises.form_notes: Retract shoulder blades, press evenly, control the descent

exercises.name: Dumbbell Row
exercises.form_notes: One hand on bench, pull to hip, squeeze shoulder blade

exercises.name: Dumbbell Overhead Press
exercises.form_notes: Press straight up from shoulders, full lockout overhead

exercises.name: Dumbbell Curl
exercises.form_notes: Alternate or together, full extension to full contraction

exercises.name: Dumbbell Lateral Raise
exercises.form_notes: Slight bend in elbows, raise to shoulder height, control descent

exercises.name: Pull-up
exercises.form_notes: Overhand grip, full dead hang to chin over bar, no kipping

exercises.name: Chin-up
exercises.form_notes: Underhand grip, full dead hang to chin over bar

exercises.name: Dip
exercises.form_notes: Lean slightly forward, lower until upper arms parallel, press up

exercises.name: Push-up
exercises.form_notes: Body straight, lower chest to floor, full lockout at top

exercises.name: Plank
exercises.form_notes: Forearms on floor, body straight, squeeze glutes and brace core

exercises.name: Lat Pulldown
exercises.form_notes: Wide grip, pull to upper chest, squeeze lats at bottom

exercises.name: Cable Row
exercises.form_notes: Sit upright, pull to lower chest, squeeze shoulder blades

exercises.name: Face Pull
exercises.form_notes: High cable, pull rope to face, externally rotate at end

exercises.name: Tricep Pushdown
exercises.form_notes: Pin elbows at sides, extend fully, squeeze triceps at bottom

exercises.name: Leg Press
exercises.form_notes: Feet shoulder-width, lower until 90 degrees, press through whole foot

exercises.name: Leg Curl
exercises.form_notes: Control the movement, full range of motion, squeeze hamstrings

exercises.name: Leg Extension
exercises.form_notes: Full extension at top, controlled descent, don't lock knees violently

exercises.name: Goblet Squat
exercises.form_notes: Hold weight at chest, elbows between knees at bottom, upright torso

exercises.name: Split Squat
exercises.form_notes: Staggered stance, lower back knee toward floor, front knee over ankle

exercises.name: Cossack Squat
exercises.form_notes: Wide stance, shift weight to one side, keep heel down, straight opposite leg

exercises.name: Split Squat Isometric
exercises.form_notes: Hold bottom position of split squat, back knee just off floor, maintain upright torso

exercises.name: Wall Sit
exercises.form_notes: Back flat against wall, thighs parallel to floor, hold for time

exercises.name: Side Lunge
exercises.form_notes: Step laterally, sit hips back, keep trailing leg straight, push back to start

exercises.name: Reverse Lunge
exercises.form_notes: Step back, lower back knee toward floor, drive through front foot to return

exercises.name: Walking Lunge
exercises.form_notes: Alternate legs stepping forward, back knee toward floor, upright torso

exercises.name: Step-Up
exercises.form_notes: Drive through top foot, stand tall at top, control descent

exercises.name: Lateral Step-Up
exercises.form_notes: Step up sideways onto box, drive through top foot, control descent

exercises.name: Step-Up with Knee Drive
exercises.form_notes: Drive through top foot, lift opposite knee high at top, control descent

exercises.name: Goblet Lateral Step-Up
exercises.form_notes: Hold dumbbell at chest, step up sideways, drive through top foot

exercises.name: Trap Bar Deadlift
exercises.form_notes: Stand inside bar, grip handles, push floor away, lock hips at top

exercises.name: Kettlebell RDL
exercises.form_notes: Slight knee bend, hinge at hips, kettlebell slides down shins, squeeze glutes at top

exercises.name: Kettlebell Staggered RDL
exercises.form_notes: Staggered stance with back foot for balance, hinge at hips, return to standing

exercises.name: Reaching Single-Leg Deadlift
exercises.form_notes: Hinge on one leg, reach hands toward floor, back leg extends behind, return to standing

exercises.name: Single-Leg Deadlift
exercises.form_notes: Hinge on one leg with weight, back leg extends behind for balance, squeeze glute at top

exercises.name: Lying Hip Extension
exercises.form_notes: Lie face down, squeeze glutes to lift legs, hold briefly at top

exercises.name: Single-Leg Hip Extension
exercises.form_notes: Lie face down, lift one leg at a time, squeeze glute at top

exercises.name: Slideboard Hamstring Curl
exercises.form_notes: Lie on back, feet on sliders, bridge up and curl heels toward glutes

exercises.name: Hamstring March
exercises.form_notes: Bridge position, alternate extending one leg at a time while maintaining hip height

exercises.name: TRX Hamstring March
exercises.form_notes: Heels in TRX straps, bridge up, alternate extending one leg while maintaining hip height

exercises.name: Weighted Push-up
exercises.form_notes: Weight plate on upper back, body straight, lower chest to floor, full lockout

exercises.name: Inverted Row
exercises.form_notes: Hang under bar or TRX, body straight, pull chest to bar, squeeze shoulder blades

exercises.name: Half-Kneeling Cable Row
exercises.form_notes: One knee down, pull cable to hip, keep torso upright and resist rotation

exercises.name: TRX Row
exercises.form_notes: Lean back holding straps, body straight, pull chest to handles, squeeze shoulder blades

exercises.name: Renegade Row
exercises.form_notes: Push-up position on dumbbells, row one arm while bracing core, alternate sides

exercises.name: Assisted Chin-up
exercises.form_notes: Use band for assistance, underhand grip, full dead hang to chin over bar

exercises.name: Band Pull-Apart
exercises.form_notes: Hold band at shoulder height, pull apart by squeezing shoulder blades, control return

exercises.name: Deadbug
exercises.form_notes: Back flat on floor, extend opposite arm and leg while maintaining core brace

exercises.name: Medicine Ball Deadbug
exercises.form_notes: Hold medicine ball between hands and knees, extend opposite arm and leg while pressing ball

exercises.name: Palloff Rotation
exercises.form_notes: Stand sideways to cable, press arms out and rotate away, resist pull back to center

exercises.name: Palloff Hold
exercises.form_notes: Stand sideways to cable, press arms out and hold, resist rotation for time

exercises.name: Hanging Knee Raise
exercises.form_notes: Hang from bar, raise knees to chest, lower with control, no swinging

exercises.name: Straight Leg Raise
exercises.form_notes: Lie on back, keep legs straight, raise to 90 degrees, lower with control

exercises.name: Standing Leg Raise Isometric
exercises.form_notes: Stand on one leg, raise other leg to hip height, hold position for time

exercises.name: TRX Mountain Climber
exercises.form_notes: Feet in TRX straps, plank position, alternate driving knees to chest

exercises.name: Stability Ball Mountain Climber
exercises.form_notes: Hands on stability ball, plank position, alternate driving knees to chest

exercises.name: Bear Crawl
exercises.form_notes: Hands and feet on floor, knees just off ground, crawl forward alternating opposite hand/foot

exercises.name: Crab Walk
exercises.form_notes: Sit, hands behind, lift hips, walk forward/backward using opposite hand/foot

programs.name: 5/3/1 for Beginners
programs.description: Wendler's 5/3/1 adapted for beginners (thefitness.wiki). Two main lifts per day with First Set Last (FSL) 5x5 supplemental. 3-week cycles. Accessories: 50-100 reps each of push, pull, and single-leg/core after main work.

programs.name: 5/3/1 BBB
programs.description: Wendler's 5/3/1 Boring But Big. Main lift followed by 5x10 supplemental at 50% training max. 3-week cycles. Accessories: 25-50 reps each of push, pull, and single-leg/core.

programs.name: Phrak's Greyskull LP
programs.description: Phrak's variant of Greyskull LP (thefitness.wiki). 3 days/week, alternating A/B workouts on a 2-week cycle. Last set is always AMRAP. Chin-ups every session.

programs.name: GZCLP
programs.description: GZCLP (Cody Lefever). 4 days/week linear progression. T1 heavy compound 5x3, T2 moderate compound 3x10, T3 light isolation 3x15. Built-in rep scheme failure protocol.

programs.name: Foundations 1×20
programs.description: Dr. Michael Yessis foundational program. 1 set of 20 reps per exercise, 2 days/week. Develops general strength, movement quality, and joint health through comprehensive full-body training. Appropriate for youth athletes and beginners. Progress by adding small weight increments when all 20 reps are completed with good form for 2+ consecutive sessions.

programs.name: Foundations 1×15
programs.description: Dr. Michael Yessis foundational program, second phase. 1 set of 15 reps per exercise, 2 days/week. Slightly more advanced exercise variations than 1×20 with increased loading potential. Athletes should complete the 1×20 phase before progressing to this program. Progress by adding small weight increments when all 15 reps are completed with good form for 2+ consecutive sessions.
